HappyShop project - client/warehouse - category

Purpose:
    manage warehouse operations, inventory monitoring, stock alerts, and provides provide staff interfacce for warehouse
    manageement and stock control

AlertSimulator
    Purpose:
    Represents a warehouse alert notification for low stock, out-of-stock items,
    or other inventory-related warnings that require staff attention.

    Properties:
    - alertId: Unique identifier for the alert
    - alertType: Type of alert (LOW_STOCK, OUT_OF_STOCK, RESTOCK_NEEDED, OVERSTOCK)
    - productId: ID of the product triggering the alert
    - productName: Name of the product
    - currentStock: Current stock quantity
    - thresholdLevel: Stock level that triggered the alert
    - severity: Alert severity (HIGH, MEDIUM, LOW)
    - timestamp: When alert was generated
    - isRead: Whether staff has viewed the alert
    - isResolved: Whether issue has been addressed
    - message: Descriptive alert message
    - assignedTo: Staff member assigned to handle alert

    Responsibilities:
    - Stores alert information
    - Provides getters/setters for alert properties
    - Determines alert priority based on severity
    - Tracks alert lifecycle (created, read, resolved)
    - Formats alert message for display

    Usage:
    Created by AlertSimulator when stock levels reach critical thresholds. Displayed
    in HistoryWindow to show past alerts. Shown in StockDashboard for real-time
    monitoring. Used by staff to track which inventory issues need attention.

HistoryWindow:
    Purpose:
    Displays historical view of all warehouse alerts, stock changes, and inventory
    events for audit trail and analysis purposes.

    Properties:
    - alertHistory: List of all historical alerts
    - dateRange: Time period being displayed
    - filterCriteria: Active filters (by product, type, severity)
    - sortOrder: How history is sorted (by date, severity, product)

    Responsibilities:
    - Displays chronological list of past alerts
    - Shows resolved and unresolved alerts
    - Provides filtering by date range, product, alert type
    - Allows sorting of alert history
    - Shows alert details (time, product, stock level, resolution)
    - Exports history to reports
    - Provides search functionality
    - Tracks who resolved each alert
    - Shows stock level trends over time

    Usage:
    Opened by warehouse staff to review past alerts and identify patterns. Used for
    auditing inventory management decisions. Helps analyze recurring stock issues.
    Accessed from WarehouseView menu or dashboard. Provides data for management
    reports.

StockDashboard:
    Purpose:
    Provides real-time overview of warehouse inventory status with visual indicators,
    active alerts, and key metrics for warehouse management.

    Properties:
    - activeAlerts: List of current unresolved alerts
    - stockLevels: Current stock quantities for all products
    - criticalItems: Products requiring immediate attention
    - dashboardMetrics: Key statistics (total items, low stock count, etc.)
    - refreshInterval: How often dashboard updates
    - alertFilters: Which alert types to display

    Responsibilities:
    - Displays real-time inventory status
    - Shows active alerts prominently
    - Provides visual indicators (colors, graphs, charts)
    - Displays key metrics (total products, low stock items, out of stock count)
    - Updates automatically as new alerts arrive
    - Allows quick navigation to problem products
    - Shows inventory trends and graphs
    - Provides summary of warehouse health
    - Enables quick actions (view details, mark as resolved)

    Usage:
    Main screen for warehouse staff monitoring operations. Always visible on
    warehouse terminals. Updates in real-time as AlertSimulator generates alerts.
    Provides at-a-glance view of inventory health. Launch point for detailed views
    and actions.

WarehouseClient
    Purpose:
    Main entry point and container for the warehouse management application,
    managing the overall warehouse staff interface and application lifecycle.

    Responsibilities:
    - Launches the warehouse application
    - Initializes all warehouse MVC components
    - Manages the main warehouse window/frame
    - Handles navigation between different warehouse screens
    - Manages application state and staff session
    - Coordinates communication between warehouse modules
    - Handles application shutdown and cleanup
    - Manages access control for warehouse staff
    - Initializes AlertSimulator background service

    Usage:
    Created and launched when warehouse staff logs in. Acts as main container for
    all warehouse functionality. Manages transitions between dashboard, stock views,
    history, and other screens. Maintains staff session throughout shift. Entry
    point for warehouse application.

WarehouseController:
    Purpose:
    Central controller that manages business logic and coordinates interactions
    between WarehouseView, WarehouseModel, and other warehouse components.

    Responsibilities:
    - Handles user actions from WarehouseView
    - Processes stock level updates
    - Manages alert acknowledgment and resolution
    - Coordinates restocking operations
    - Handles product searches and filters
    - Updates view based on model changes
    - Validates staff input before processing
    - Manages error handling and user feedback
    - Coordinates with AlertSimulator for monitoring
    - Processes bulk inventory operations

    Usage:
    Created by WarehouseClient during initialization. Receives all user interactions
    from WarehouseView. Calls WarehouseModel for data operations. Updates
    WarehouseView based on results. Acts as central coordinator for all warehouse
    operations.

WarehouseModel:
    Purpose:
    Manages warehouse data, inventory information, and communicates with the server
    to retrieve stock levels, process updates, and maintain warehouse state.

    Responsibilities:
    - Stores current inventory data for all products
    - Retrieves stock levels from database
    - Updates stock quantities after restocking
    - Processes inventory adjustments
    - Maintains alert data and history
    - Communicates with server APIs
    - Validates inventory operations
    - Tracks stock movements (in/out)
    - Manages reorder points and thresholds
    - Handles data persistence and caching

    Usage:
    Called by WarehouseController to perform data operations. Communicates with
    server-side APIs and database. Maintains warehouse inventory state. Provides
    data to controller which updates the view. Handles all business logic related
    to warehouse operations.

WarehouseUIStyles:
    Purpose:
    Defines visual styling, themes, colors, and layout constants for the warehouse
    interface to ensure consistent UI design throughout the warehouse application.

    Properties:
    - Color scheme: Professional warehouse interface colors
    - Alert colors: Red (critical), yellow (warning), green (ok)
    - Font families: Clear, readable fonts for warehouse environment
    - Font sizes: Large enough for quick reading from distance
    - Button styles: Large buttons for touch-screen terminals
    - Spacing constants: Generous spacing for usability
    - Border styles: Clear borders for sections
    - Icon sizes: Large icons for quick recognition
    - Chart colors: Color-coded graphs and metrics
    - Dashboard layouts: Grid-based dashboard design

    Responsibilities:
    - Provides consistent color palette for warehouse interface
    - Defines alert color coding (red, yellow, green)
    - Ensures visual consistency across all warehouse views
    - Makes UI customization centralized and maintainable
    - Supports high-contrast mode for warehouse lighting
    - Defines layout for dashboards and data displays
    - Provides accessibility-compliant design

    Usage:
    Used by WarehouseView to style all UI components consistently. Applied when
    creating buttons, panels, dashboards, and alerts. Ensures entire warehouse
    application has professional, easy-to-read appearance. Makes global style
    changes easy.

WarehouseView
    Purpose:
    Provides the graphical user interface for warehouse staff, displaying inventory
    levels, alerts, stock dashboard, and all warehouse management screens.

    UI Components:
    - Stock dashboard with real-time metrics
    - Active alerts panel with color-coded indicators
    - Product inventory list with stock levels
    - Search and filter controls
    - Stock level indicators (visual bars/gauges)
    - Restock buttons and forms
    - Alert acknowledgment buttons
    - History view access
    - Charts and graphs for trends
    - Quick action toolbar
    - Staff menu and navigation

    Responsibilities:
    - Renders all warehouse UI screens
    - Displays StockDashboard with real-time updates
    - Shows active alerts with appropriate colors
    - Provides inventory search and filtering
    - Captures user input and actions
    - Sends events to WarehouseController
    - Updates display based on controller commands
    - Applies WarehouseUIStyle to all components
    - Provides smooth navigation between screens
    - Shows loading states during operations
    - Displays confirmation and error messages

    Usage:
    Created by WarehouseClient during initialization. Controlled by
    WarehouseController. Displays all warehouse-facing screens and captures user
    interactions. Sends events to controller. Updated by controller based on model
    changes. Applies WarehouseUIStyle for consistent appearance. Staff's main
    interface for warehouse operations.